To run the Android application the following steps must be foloowed - 

1.) Install Android Studio with the latest version of Google Play Services. 
2.) Download the project - program.zip and unzip it. 
3.) Import the project. 
4.) In Android Studio go to Build -> Make project. 
5.) Then click on Build -> Deploy Module to App engine. 
6.) Connect an Android device with USB debugging enabled, to the coomputer/laptop.
7.) Click on the run button in the toolbar (The green triange).
8.) In the "Select Deployment Target" window that opens, choose the connected device and click OK.
9.) The application may take some time to build and deploy to the device. 
10.) Once step 9 is completed, the application will open on the android device.